   STerm - A simple and minimalistic terminal emulator based on VTE-2.90
===========================================================================

Requirements
------------

 * glib2
 * GTK+-3.0
 * VTE-2.90
 * cmake >= 2.8.8

Installation
------------

mkdir build
cd build
cmake [OPTIONS] ..
make
su -c "make install"

CMake options:

 -DWITH_LIBRARY={ON,OFF}   Build the shared library libsterm-core.so ?
                           Default: ON
 -DWITH_URLPIPE={ON,OFF}   Build the sterm-urlpipe binary ?
                           Default: ON

Usage
-----

The example configuration file (sterm.ini) is located in the source
directory and gets installed to /usr/share/doc/sterm/.
Copy the file to ~/.config/sterm/sterm.ini and adapt it to your needs.

Run 'sterm --help-all' to see all possible arguments.

Basic arguments:
 -c FILE    Use a different configuration file.
 -e COMMAND Run the given command in the new terminal.


